    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d12fn1">Sent by the United States Military Attaché, London,
                        via Army channels. For other excerpts from this telegram, see <hi
                            rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_159">pp. 159</ref>–<ref
                            target="#pg_160">160</ref>, <ref target="#pg_206">206</ref>, <ref
                            target="#pg_328">328</ref>, <ref target="#pg_400">400</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Excerpts]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-22">22 October
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>
                    Personal and Top Secret Number 801.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Para 8. I was delighted to hear from U. J. that you had suggested a triple
                    meeting towards the end of November at a Black Sea port. I think this a very
                    fine idea, and hope you will let me know about it in due course. I will come
                    anywhere you two desire.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
